<h3><a name="nav-template"></a>Navigation Template</h3>
<h4>Purpose</h4>
<p>The navigation template defines the overall structure for the navigation and sub-navigation.
   WalkerCMS uses the output from this template to fill both the <span class="variable-name">nav</span>
   and <span class="variable-name">sub_nav</span> variables in the primary template.</p>
<p>Though two different variables are filled using this template, the data that gets pushed into the
   variables below is different depending on whether the main navigation is being populated or
   the page sub-navigation. When you create your navigation template, ensure that it is generic
   enough to handle both cases.</p>
<h4>Usage</h4>
<p>The navigation template has a filename of &quot;nav_template.php&quot; and is required to be present
   for a website using WalkerCMS.</p>
<p>It is possible to use any valid PHP in the template as long as it is surrounded by any of the
   possible PHP tags.</p>
<h4>Available Variables</h4>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Variable</th>
      <th>Data&nbsp;Type</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">is_primary_nav</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether WalkerCMS is current generating the primary navigation or
           sub-navigation.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">nav_items</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains a list of <span class="markup-tag">&lt;li&gt;</span> elements that WalkerCMS has
           generated from the configuration given whether it is the primary navigation or
           sub-navigation./p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">organization_name</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the familiar name of the organization for which you are creating a website.
           This value comes directly from the site configuration.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
